Antofagasta, LSE, Rank Group Plc: U.K., Irish Equity Preview

-- B y   B l a n c h e   G a t t
-- 
2011-06-28T23:00:01Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-06-28/antofagasta-lse-rank-group-plc-u-k-irish-equity-preview.html
The following is a list of companies
that may have unusual share-price changes in U.K. and Irish
markets. Stock symbols are in parentheses and prices are from
the last market close.  The FTSE 100 Index advanced 44.54 points, or 0.8 percent,
to 5,766.88. The FTSE All-Share Index rose 0.7 percent to
3,005.85, while Ireland’s ISEQ Index advanced 0.9 percent to
2,912.05.  Antofagasta Plc (ANTO)  : The copper producer controlled
by Chile’s Luksic family sees “huge demand” for metals as
 China  and other emerging markets invest in infrastructure and
urbanization, Chief Executive Officer Jean Paul Luksic said in
an interview in  London . The shares gained 1.6 percent to 1,303
pence.  Betfair Group Plc (BET)  : The British Internet gaming
site may report full-year net income of 14.5 million pounds
($23.2 million), according to the average of four estimates
compiled by Bloomberg. The shares jumped 6.2 percent to 771.5
pence.  London Stock Exchange Group Plc (LSE)  : Luc Bertrand, who
leads a group of banks and pension funds bidding for TMX Group
Inc., said he’s confident TMX shareholders will reject a bid
from the London Stock Exchange Group for the owner of the
Toronto Stock Exchange. Bertrand spoke to reporters in Toronto.
LSE’s stock dropped 1.1 percent to 927 pence.  Rank Group Plc (RNK)  : The U.K.-based casino and online
gambling operator’s independent directors recommended
shareholders accept an offer from Guoco Group Ltd., even though
they consider the offer to “substantially undervalue Rank.”
The stock retreated 0.2 percent to 149.6 pence.  Stagecoach Group Plc (SGC LN): The operator of Britain’s
busiest commuter-rail service may report full-year net income of
178.8 million pounds, according to the average of six estimates
compiled by Bloomberg. The stock rose 1 percent to 250.2 pence.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Blanche Gatt in London at 
